---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE, SOCIAL } from "../consts";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About · Oracaus"
  description="Przemyslaw Kalka, front-end systems engineer working on real-time risk and trading interfaces."
>
  <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">About</h1>
  <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 leading-relaxed text-fg-muted">
    <p>
      I'm <span class="font-bold">{SITE.author}</span>, a front-end systems
      engineer based in London, building real-time risk and trading interfaces
      across FX, fixed income, derivatives, and commodities.
    </p>
    <p>
      That corner of front-end has its own physics. Input rate, render rate, and
      compute rate are three separate clocks. p99 frame time matters more than
      the mean. A worker round-trip, a GC pause, or a stale async result can
      each put a number on screen the market never held. Most of it lives as
      desk folklore rather than written method. I work at the seam of two things
      that rarely sit together, trading-desk domain and front-end systems depth,
      and that combination is what this site is about.
    </p>
    <p>
      I write here about profiling and fixing interfaces that never stop
      updating, and turn the methods into <a
        href="/work"
        class="text-accent-info hover:underline">open-source projects</a
      > you can read and run. Open to senior front-end systems engineering roles,
      and to consulting on real-time UI architecture and performance. The fastest
      way to reach me is <a
        href={SOCIAL.linkedin}
        class="text-accent-info hover:underline">LinkedIn</a
      >.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
